OL,3,C'I heard popping': police describe
OL,4,Cnight of Lyra's death
OL,6,FThis officer confirmed that following
OL,7,Fthis, officers moved to the junction,
OL,8,Fset up a police cordon and observed
OL,9,Fspent casings which were left in situ
OL,10,Ffor Crime Scene Investigators.
OL,12,FThe third and final officer called to
OL,13,Fthe witness stand was also asked what
OL,14,Fhe saw and heard that evening.
OL,16,FAfter confirming the vehicle he was in
OL,17,Fon Fanad Drive was attacked with
OL,18,Fmissiles including petrol bombs and
OL,19,Ffireworks, the constable was asked
OL,20,F"what could you see from your
OL,21,Fposition?"
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/14
